70 when you said: ‘The age is renewed;
71 justice and the first human time return,
72 and a new lineage descends from heaven’.

76 Already the whole world was pregnant
77 with the true faith, sown
78 by the messengers of the eternal kingdom;

79 and your word touched on above
80 was in harmony with the new preachers;
81 whence I took it upon myself to visit them often.

82 Then they seemed to me so holy,
83 that when Domitian persecuted them,
84 their lamentations were not without my tears;

88 And before I led the Greeks to the rivers
89 of Thebes in my poetry, I received baptism;
90 but through fear I remained a secret Christian,

91 outwardly showing paganism for a long time;
92 and this lukewarmness made me circle the fourth circle
93 more than the fourth hundredth.

