115 Both poets were now silent,
116 newly attentive to looking around,
117 free from climbing and from walls;

130 But the sweet discourse was soon interrupted
131 by a tree that we found in the middle of the road,
132 with fragrant and delicious apples to smell;

139 The two poets approached the tree;
140 and a voice from within the leaves
141 cried out: “You will be sorry for this food”.

151 Honey and locusts were the food
152 that nourished the Baptist in the desert;
